CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1962, pg. 4 reads: "Standing For Right - Six of the group of Penn Hills clergymen, united to fight swimming-pool segregation, are (left to right) the Revs. E. Earl Anderson, William McCartney, John Blewitt, Rudolph Unger, Robert Bolt and Donald C. Book. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six clergymen, from left: Rev. E. Earl Anderson, Rev. William McCartney, Rev. John Blewitt, Rev. Rudolph Unger, Rev. Robert Bolt, and Rev. Donald C. Book, standing in front of Penn Hills Presbyterian Church, closer version
